Author: willarson
Content: I read this article in the WSJ this morning. Sprint released users who were essentially abusing the system (making on average 25 calls per month). These thousand users were probably not profitable for Sprint with their increased strain on the tech support. I think this is a reasonable course of action for Sprint, and it ought to benefit the remaining Sprint customers.
